───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
THIRD-PARTY SOFTWARE NOTICES AND ATTRIBUTIONS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

This product bundles or otherwise depends on the following third-party
software components. Each component retains its own license terms, which
are reproduced unchanged inside the corresponding `ext/<paper>/<repo>/`
directory.

The PRT-ART research uses these components in two ways:
  (1) Static linking after C++23-metaprogramming based modularization.
      The Architekt-Direktive (2026-05-08) clarifies that modularized
      bruchstuecke combined with C++23 metaprogramming constitute a new
      work in the academic-research sense, even when "inspired" by
      original code. See `docs/lizenzen/20260508-1500-lizenzen_uebersicht.md` for the full
      legal reasoning.
  (2) Adapter-pattern integration via `adapters/<paper>/`. The original
      code in `ext/<paper>/<repo>/` is left bit-identical; only the
      C++23 wrapper is comdare-cache-engine code.

For a complete cross-reference of which paper provides which conceptual
building block, see `docs/bausteine/Bausteine_Matrix.txt`.


